definitions.definition: A mathematical set that has a non- integer and constant Hausdorff dimension , corresponding to a geometric figure or object that is self-similar at arbitrarily small scales and thus has infinite complexity .
An object, system, or idea that exhibits a fractal-like property, such as the property of self-similarity at numerous but not infinitely many scales.

main_definition: ( mathematics ) A mathematical set that has a non- integer and constant Hausdorff dimension , corresponding to a geometric figure or object that is self-similar at arbitrarily small scales and thus has infinite complexity .
secondary_definitions: ( by extension ) An object, system, or idea that exhibits a fractal-like property, such as the property of self-similarity at numerous but not infinitely many scales.
